# List.slice on the native VM

Regression for the `List.slice` arm of `v2-imported-receiver-methods-not-linked`:
the v2 native runtime had `take`/`drop` but no `slice`, so `xs.slice(a, b)`
returned `Stub` on the VM/ASM lanes while the interpreter computed it.

```scalascript
val xs = List(10, 20, 30, 40, 50)
println(xs.slice(1, 4))
println(xs.slice(0, 2))
println(xs.slice(3, 99))
```
